observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor to instruct the:
• Municipal Treasurer/GSO to conduct complete RCPPE on the basis of the prescribed format and submit the RPCPPE to the Audit Team not later than January 31 of each year;
• municipal treasurer and OIC municipal accountant to reconcile the difference noted between the RPCPPE and the accounting records in order not to compromise the reliability of submitted reports;
• municipal treasurer/accountant to exhaust all efforts to fully identify the PPEs included in the beginning balances/unidentified missing, donated, sold and unserviceable to arrive at the correct balance in the financial statements. As to the infrastructure assets, coordinate with the Municipal Engineer to verify their existence, prepare and maintain the required Property Cards and update the ARE to facilitate the reconciliation of RPCPPE with the accounting records;
• the accounting department to secure the necessary documents/records that will support the balances of PPEs to be able to reconcile with the Inventory Report of the GSO. Also, trace those PPEs without depreciation and with negative balances to establish their correct carrying value. Likewise, review the composition of the accounts under those PPEs and identify the appropriate classification for those items identified in the audit and effect necessary adjusting entries; and
• the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant as the designated GSO to maintain complete and updated PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards, respectively, to facilitate the reconciliation of both records.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
• Municipal Treasurer to prepare the breakdown of the total delinquent taxes as to the principal amount, interest and penalty to come with a comparable data with that of the Municipal Accountant’s record;
• Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile the balances of RPT and SET Receivables and the total delinquency taxes and effect the necessary adjustments, if any;
• Municipal Accountant to adopt the new guidelines in recording the total amount collectible at the beginning of the year; and
• Municipal Treasurer to monitor payment of real property tax due for the current year and exhaust all efforts and devise strategies to collect all delinquent real property taxes.

We reiterated our previous years’ recommendations that:
• The LGU create Office of the GSO, if possible, and also an Inventory Committee to conduct complete inventory taking of all the Municipal properties particularly on those not included in the last year, prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and submit to the Municipal Accountant and Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of every year;
• Make strategic actions/plan on how to conduct a complete physical inventory of all Municipal properties, engage and adopt all the necessary means to accomplish the task/plan accordingly;
• The General Services Officer or the Assistant Municipal Treasurer exert more effort to reconcile Inventory Report and Property records with that of the Accounting records. Require person responsible/accountable to request for relief from accountability to the Commission on Audit for those properties that are missing and could not be accounted for;
• The Municipal Accountant and the GSO/Property Officer/Assistant Municipal Treasurer maintain complete and updated PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards, respectively, to facilitate the reconciliation of both records; and
• The Municipal Accountant record all the donated properties in the books and the Municipal Budget appropriate in its annual budget the cost of transfer and titling of the 18 parcels of land in the name of the Municipality.

We reiterated our previous years’ recommendations that:
The LGU create Office of the GSO, if possible,  and also an   Inventory Committee to conduct complete inventory taking of all the Municipal properties particularly on those not included in the last year, prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and submit to the Municipal Accountant and Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of every year;
The General Services Officer reconcile Inventory Report and Property records with that of the Accounting records. Require person responsible/accountable to request for relief from accountability to the Commission on Audit  for those properties that are missing and could not be accounted for;
The Municipal Accountant and the GSO/Property Officer maintain complete and updated PPE Ledger Cards and Property Cards, respectively, to facilitate the reconciliation of both records; and
The Municipal Accountant draw journal entry voucher to transfer to the barangays  the donated Motor Vehicles,  record all the donated Land in the books of the municipality and the Municipal Budget appropriate in its annual budget the cost of transfer and titling of the 18 parcels of land in the name of the municipal government.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
ensure that all mechanisms and processes for gender mainstreaming are in place for the implementation of Magna Carta of Women;
create monitoring and evaluation team that will determine if policies, structures, systems and mechanisms were put in place to institutionalize the pursuit of gender equality and women’s empowerment;
ensure that projects embodied in the GAD Plan and Budget do address specific gender issues; and
exert extra efforts in establishing the GAD database as basis for planning, budgeting and policy formulation in accordance with the mandated of PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01 or Guidelines on the Localization of the Magna Carta of Women.
